\pard\plain \tx0\sa120\sb120\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Ps::0>[  When refining/rewriting the first two paragraphs of narrative, it might be a good idea to provide more detail about what Evan did in the hour he was waiting to return to the girls. This might include a description of the location as defined in the scene profile \endash  the Riverwalk of Naperville. Evan spent much of his time exploring the Riverwalk.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 Also you might mention, that he stopped by the fall festival to check it out. Use your judgment, this is only a suggestion.]<!$Scr_Ps::0><$Scr_Ps::1>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\fi360\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 The last hour felt like four hours to Evan. He felt like an idiot for the way he interrupted Maggie and Laura\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s dinner. All the confidence he had earlier in the day was gone. Evan tried not to be too down on himself. He realized if he had not taken a chance with Maggie, he would be beating himself up for being a coward. Luckily the hour was over. He would know soon enough what the results would be.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 When Evan turned the corner, his mood quickly turned upward. There he saw two smiling women waiting for him. <!$Scr_Ps::1>}
\par\pard\plain \sa120\sl264\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Relieved, courteously ensuring Laura that she is also invited):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 I\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92m so glad you\u8217\'92re here. I was sweating there for a while. I checked out the festival, and it looks like a lot of fun. Are you ladies ready?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Laura<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Excited for Maggie):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93You have a good time! Text me when you\u8217\'92re ready to be picked up.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>[ Laura grabbed Maggie by the shoulders and passed her off to Evan like she was a baton in a relay race. ]<!$Scr_Cs::3>}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Laura<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6   }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Saying as she walks away, leaving Evan and Maggie to enjoy their date without her):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Take good care of my girl.\u8221\'94}
\par\pard\plain \tx9000\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch {\f4\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf6 \~\tab }
\par\pard\plain \sa120\sl264\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Sincere, excited, hopeful):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Thank you for giving me a chance. I have a feeling Laura was cheerleading for me after I left.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(happy but with mild apprehension):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93She was definitely rooting for you. Before we head out, can we chat a bit?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(accommodating):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Absolutely. I know a spot that\u8217\'92s just perfect for us.\u8221\'94}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\sa120\sb120\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Ps::0>[ Having explored the area for an hour before returning to the girls, Evan had a good idea where they could chat. Evan took Maggie to a quiet bench facing the river, far away from the noise of the crowded fair. ]<!$Scr_Ps::0>}
\par\pard\plain \tx6768\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(gesturing is arms  and hands toward the bench):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Will this work?\u8221\'94\tab }
\par\pard\plain \sa120\sl264\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Pleased as they both sat down.):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93This is perfect.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Wanting to clear the tiny bit of her skepticism remaining):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93I wanted to ask you something, Evan. I want you to be honest. I give you credit for being creative if you made up that story, but I would like to know if it\u8217\'92s true. \u8220\'93}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\sa120\sb120\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3><$Scr_Ps::0>[ Insert a narrative here before Evan speaks.<!$Scr_Cs::3>}
\par\plain \f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>Evan thought about her question for a brief moment. He remembered that he told Liz that he wouldn\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u8217\'92t have to lie but simply leave out the fact that his intention is to break up after one year. Evan recounted what he had told Maggie about the universe guiding him toward her and determined that every word was indeed true. This gave him the mental impression he needed to feel sincere in the dialogue that follows. ]<!$Scr_Cs::3><!$Scr_Ps::0>}
\par\pard\plain \sa120\sl264\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch \f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Sincerely):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Honestly, I couldn\u8217\'92t make that up if I tried. It\u8217\'92s all true.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Curious):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s not important. But I\u8217\'92m curious, how old you are? I\u8217\'92m 26.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>:<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m 29.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Earnestly impressed):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93I checked out your company\u8217\'92s website. You\u8217\'92ve achieved a lot for your age.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Grateful for her comments, humbly acknowledging others):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Thank you. I had a lot of help from a brilliant business partner, my sister, and a great team. I couldn\u8217\'92t have accomplished any of it without them.\u8221\'94}
\par\pard\plain \tx9000\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch {\f4\fs24\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\cf6 \~\tab }
\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch \f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6
\par\pard\plain \sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 Maggie}{\f4\fs24\b0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 (Generally impressed, making her even more curious why Evan is single.):}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93It is impressive. I think it\u8217\'92s a good idea to get to know each other better. I have to ask, why is a guy like you single?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\i0\cf5 Evan}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 (Sincere):}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m not a fan of playing the dating game, especially first dates,}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6 and I\loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8217\'92m no good at it. It\u8217\'92s like there\u8217\'92s all these unwritten rules that I don\u8217\'92t understand. But I am pretty sure I\u8217\'92m about to break one.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\i0\cf5 Maggie}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 (intrigued):}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Go for it!\u8221\'94}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\sa120\sb120\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Ps::0>}
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 [ Insert narrative here before Evan speaks.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 Evan rarely confides in anybody about painful memories. Especially when it comes to discussing his divorce and his ex-wife Sarah. However, he realizes that if he wants to have a relationship with Maggie, sooner or later he\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s going to have to divulge the fact that he was divorced over a year ago. Plus, he wants to get out of the way so he doesn\u8217\'92t have to think about it anymore.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 However, he wants to keep the mood light. This is his purpose for playfully admitting he\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s breaking a first date rule. He wants to hide his pain from Maggie.]<!$Scr_Ps::0>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch \f0\fs26\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \sa120\sl264\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Hiding his pain with playfulness):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93I know people aren\u8217\'92t supposed to talk about exes on their first date. But I wanted to be upfront with you from the start. I was married for several years and got divorced a little bit over a year ago. How bad of a first-date violation was that?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Reassuring, sharing her disdain for the lack of sincerity that often accompanies a first date):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93You have nothing to worry about with me. I despise first-date etiquette. I don\u8217\'92t understand why people can\u8217\'92t be authentic from the start.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Relieved, feeling a stronger connection in Maggie's validation):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93That\u8217\'92s a relief. Ever since my divorce, I\u8217\'92ve been on a string of dates with no spark. It\u8217\'92s been rough. Even worse when friends set you up, and you feel obligated for a second date.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Validating, resigned):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Believe me, I understand. I\u8217\'92ve had my fair share of online dating nightmares, too. But honestly, my main issue is time. Between culinary school and work, I\u8217\'92m swamped.\u8221\'94}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\sa120\sb120\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Ps::0>[ Have Maggie sigh or pause between the lines of dialogue. As much as she likes Evan, she's pretty sure which is about to tell him will dissuade him from pursuing a relationship with her. ]<!$Scr_Ps::0>}
\par\pard\plain \sa120\sl264\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(resigned):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93I go to culinary school five days a week in the morning, and I work as a line cook six, sometimes seven, nights a week. My only free time is a few hours in the afternoon and sometimes on Sundays.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Sincere):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93I think that\u8217\'92s great! I admire people who work hard to better their lives.\u8221\'94}
\par\pard\plain \tx9000\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs24\b1\i0\ul\ulc0\cf6 \~\tab }
\par\pard\plain \sa120\sl264\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch \f3\fs24\b1\i0\cf6
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Resigned, certain Evan will no longer be interested):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93That\u8217\'92s very kind of you to say. Evan, you are incredibly charming, and I like you. But I think our time together is going to be limited to tonight. I\u8217\'92ll understand if you don\u8217\'92t want to go to the festival together.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Uncertain if Maggie is just letting him down gently):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Please be candid - no need to spare my feelings. If you didn\u8217\'92t have such a busy schedule, would you be interested in exploring a relationship with me?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Reassuring, but still a bit apprehensive):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Don't misunderstand me, Evan. I think you're great, and I\u8217\'92d jump at the chance to see where this might go. I think that\u8217\'92s what scares me the most. I\u8217\'92ve been dumped by a boyfriend who complained I didn\u8217\'92t see him enough. I don\u8217\'92t want to get too attached and then have that happen again.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>[ Insert narrative here before Evan speaks.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 Evan had not prepared any sort of speech ahead of time. He was flying by the "seat of his pants" so to speak. A fond memory popped into his head. He remembered his first date with Sarah. Sarah had approached their first date like a business meeting. Like Maggie, Sarah had a busy schedule, and like Evan, Sarah had little interest in playing the dating game. Sarah a business major, and trained by her father in the art of contract negotiations, approached the date as if her and Evan were negotiating a business partnership. While this might have sent most men running, Evan loves Sarah's approach. He happily agreed to Sarah's "relationship/partnership conditions." He admired Sarah's attempt to make sure they were fair to both of them.<!$Scr_Cs::3>}
\par\plain \f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>Evan was hoping that seeing Maggie's reaction to sharing details of his first date with Sarah, would give him an indication on her readiness to do something similar \endash  albeit less business-like.  ]<!$Scr_Cs::3>}
\par\plain \f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(fondly reliving his first date was Sarah):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93I remember this one date during my college years, it was pretty out of the ordinary. She was a busy business major, and we had a spark. Instead of the usual dating dance, she suggested we just start a relationship right there and then. It was like we were negotiating a partnership.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Giggling, interjected):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Talk about breaking first-date rules.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Eyes widened as he enthusiastically continued):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93I know, right? But it was great! She did a good job of laying out all the expectations upfront. She told me what she had to offer and what she expected from me and then opened it up for discussion. I know it sounds unromantic, but it felt the opposite. I was pleasantly surprised, to say the least.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Laughing, but then realizing Evan's purpose in telling the story hinted at something more):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Seriously? That's amusing yet fascinating. Are you suggesting we take a similar approach.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Excited that Maggie understood is intent behind the story and seemed open to the idea):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93That\u8217\'92s precisely what I am suggesting!\u8221\'94}
