\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 I think this is an important point we need to get across to the readers as the scene unfolds. What's about to happen in the next several scene segments, is that Maggie, convinced that her concerns are unresolvable, begins shooting obstacles in Evan's direction. }
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 However, in Evan's mind everything she is saying is even more confirmation that the universe had picked her. He mentally refers back to the rules Liz prepared. }
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 In this scene segment, Evan sees Maggie's busy schedule as conducive to keeping in line with the rule not to get integrated into her inner circle of friends and family  \endash  there simply won't be enough time. He also perceives that their minimal time together will prevent her from getting too attached and make the breakup easier when the years over. Granted, Evan is trying to convince himself that this is true, without necessarily believing it to be true.  }
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 Additionally, the readers will begin to see Evan's "problem-solving" skills. In life and in business, Evan naturally kicks into problem-solving mode when he sees a situation that needs attention.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 ]<!$Scr_Ps::0>}
\par\pard\plain \sa120\sl264\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch \f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Optimistic problem-solving):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Your schedule may not be as problematic as you think. I have a busy schedule, too, and I spend a lot of time traveling as part of my efforts for my foundation. Since we both have busy schedules, neither one of us will complain about it. Plus, I think there\u8217\'92s a silver lining to seeing each other less often than we\u8217\'92d like.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Intrigued):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93A silver lining?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Optimistic):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Yes. If we always leave each other wanting more, think how excited we will be every time we see each other! What\u8217\'92s more important in any relationship than being excited to see your partner?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Impressed with Evan's perspective, but still apprehensive, throwing another obstacle his way):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92ve got to say, Evan, I never thought about it like that. I like the way you think. But even if we can work that out, I have another huge concern.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Now in problem-solving mode, he's ready to resolve any concern.):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m sure we can find a solution. What\u8217\'92s your concern?\u8221\'94}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\sa120\sb120\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Ps::0>[ FYI: In the next several segments of the scene, Maggie's stress regarding money and finances begins to show itself. Later in the story, we see how this recurring fear she has's money impacts her life.]<!$Scr_Ps::0>}
\par\pard\plain \sa120\sl264\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Apprehensive):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Based on what I saw on the Internet. I think it\u8217\'92s safe to assume you have money. Unfortunately, I have an issue with money.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>:<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93What\u8217\'92s the issue?\u8220\'93}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(An exasperating tone, half-joke, half-serious):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93My issue is, I don\u8217\'92t have any. \u8220\'93 }
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>[Evan giggled at Maggie's semi-joke] <!$Scr_Cs::3>}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie <!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Continuing, stress evident in her tone):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6   \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93 I barely get by working six days a week, and just thinking about money stresses me out. Last year, I dated a guy with money. It didn\u8217\'92t work out,\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6 : \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93May I ask why?\u8221\'94}
