\par\pard\plain \sa120\sl264\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch \f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(reliving her unpleasant experience):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93He would always take me to these fancy restaurants. I cringed at the thought of how much he was spending. I would always look away when the check came. I think that annoyed him because one day, he made sure I knew how much it cost. Oh my God, Evan, between the wine and the food, the bill was enough to pay my electricity for months. I couldn\u8217\'92t even enjoy the food anymore.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Interjecting with the role of his eyes):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Flaunting his wealth, I know the type.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Continued, unpleasantness of her past experience affected in her tone):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93It wasn\u8217\'92t just that. I don\u8217\'92t think he liked the way I dressed. He would shower me with gifts of designer clothes and shoes. I don\u8217\'92t wear that stuff. He ignored my request to stop giving me these gifts. So, I decided to return what I could and use the money to pay bills. Anything I couldn\u8217\'92t return, I gave to Laura. She was getting more out of that relationship than I was. The guy found out what I was doing and broke up with me.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Sincere, validating):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93That guy was a jerk. A woman should wear what she\u8217\'92s comfortable wearing, not what the man wants her to wear. It\u8217\'92s one thing for a man to give a woman a gift because of how he feels about her. However, it\u8217\'92s quite another thing to repeatedly give her unwanted gifts. \u8221\'94}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\sa120\sb120\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Ps::0>[ Maggie doesn't say anything between these two lines of dialogue from Evan, but I want the reader to see that she's relieved to get that off her chest, and gives Evan a warm smile seeing that he understands the situation. Another aspect of her relief, is that she senses that Evan is the opposite of the wealthy man she dated in the past. ]<!$Scr_Ps::0>}
\par\pard\plain \sa120\sl264\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Thoughtful trying to get a better understanding):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93I am curious, though. Being a culinary student, wouldn\u8217\'92t you enjoy going to all types of restaurants - even expensive ones? I enjoy expensive restaurants as much as I enjoy a good mom-and-pop hotdog joint.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Trying to understand it herself):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Well... I suppose. I guess because I\u8217\'92m always so broke, fine dining feels like such a waste of money.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(inquiring, Collecting more information needed to resolve this issue):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93So, if money was not a factor, would you enjoy going to more expensive restaurants occasionally, or would you consider that an unwelcome gift?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Answering Evan question):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93If money were no object, I would love to try all types of restaurants. I plan to get a job at a high-end restaurant when I get my culinary degree. They\u8217\'92ll pay a lot more than I make now, and then I can save money for my ultimate dream.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>:<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93And that is?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Her dreams bring a sparkle to her eyes):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93I want to own an Irish pub one day. A place where regular folk can get good food without breaking the bank.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Genuinely enthusiastic):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93I love that idea! Most pubs I\u8217\'92ve visited around town seem to deep-fry everything.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Enjoying Evan's response to her dream):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Yep! Straight from the freezer. I want my place to be different - fresh comfort food at a place that feels like home.\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Energizing):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92d be first in line!\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Ready to lay out his proposed solution):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93I have a great idea that will resolve all your concerns.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Intrigued):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93I don\u8217\'92t see how, but lay it on me!\u8221\'94}
