\par\plain \f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 I want an effective narrative to reflect Evan's feelings and thoughts before he proposes his ideas to Maggie. I like you to integrate some internal dialogue as part of the narrative. Make the narrative as long or short as you like, it doesn't need to be limited to one paragraph you feel it needs more.}
\par\plain \f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 Here are the thoughts I like to convey before Evan proposes his solutions.}
\par\plain \f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4  Evan is feeling very good about how this is all playing out. He feels that Maggie situation is a perfect fit for his relationship plan.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4   1. Her busy schedule will prevent them from getting too close.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4   2. The distance between them ensuring they won't run into each other during or after the breakup.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4   3. He generally feels that he can add value to Maggie's life. Keep in mind, Evan worked hard to get where he is, but he embraces a life that prioritizes enjoyment of life.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4   4. Problem solver Evan, feels this will be a win-win for them both. His mind is not on the ultimate pain of the breakup, but of the positive aspects prior to the inevitable breakup. }{\f1\fs22\b0\i1\cf4 ]<!$Scr_Ps::0>}
\par\pard\plain \sa120\sl264\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch \f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Problem solver Evan begins to lay out his plan):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Here\u8217\'92s what I propose. When I\u8217\'92m not traveling, my schedule is very flexible. Since your free time is limited to afternoon hours, that\u8217\'92s when we will spend our time together. I\u8217\'92ve always wanted to learn to cook, so why don\u8217\'92t we do this. You teach me how to cook. I\u8217\'92ll buy the proteins and other expensive ingredients. You can supply the kitchen and the spices and other basics. We can hang out at your place, cook together, watch movies, and do whatever other fun stuff we can squeeze into the hours between school and work. How does that sound so far?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Struggling to believe the wonderful things she's hearing, her skepticism returns):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93It sounds too good to be true. You\u8217\'92d really be willing to drive all the way out here during the week just to see me for a few hours?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Sincere, excited):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Absolutely! Although I hope to squeeze a few Sundays in there now and then. I have a great idea about expanding your dining horizons.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Enjoying this ride):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Let\u8217\'92s hear it!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Continuing with his plan):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Let\u8217\'92s try to go out for a meal once a week or as often as our schedules allow. We\u8217\'92ll each take turns choosing a restaurant. There will be times when I\u8217\'92ll pick an expensive restaurant, and there will be times when I opt for something inexpensive. When it\u8217\'92s your turn, you can choose whatever restaurant you like. As far as money goes, as much as you are concerned about money, I am the opposite. I don\u8217\'92t care about money at all.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Mostly joking, but with a hint of realization in its truth):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93That\u8217\'92s because you have it.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Reflective, sincere):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93That\u8217\'92s true, but it wasn\u8217\'92t always that way. I spent much of my childhood living with a single mom, working two jobs to make ends meet. I learned that I could enjoy life, with or without money.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>[ Hearing of Evan's pre-wealth past and connecting with his mother's plight of having to work two jobs to make ends meet, Maggie felt her skepticism begin to fade away and her connection with Evan to strengthen significantly. ]<!$Scr_Cs::3>}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>Maggie<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::3>(Resigned):<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f4\fs24\b0\i0\cf6  \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93I understand that, but it\u8217\'92s hard to maintain that perspective when rent is due.\u8221\'94}
